Tentura — licensing notice

Effective date: 19 July 2026

Tentura contains material under more than one compatible GNU copyleft
license. This notice records the applicable licensing boundary; it does not
transfer anybody's copyright or authorship.

If a file or component carries its own license notice, SPDX identifier, or
third-party license, that specific notice controls. Otherwise, the following
rules apply.

1. Legacy GPL material

Copyrightable material owned by Alexander Postnikov, Dmitrii Sosnin, Angelina
Ermakova, or another contributor other than Vadim Bulavintsev remains licensed
under the GNU General Public License, version 3 or (at the recipient's option)
any later version (GPL-3.0-or-later), to the extent that material was governed
by the repository's previous GPL notice. Nothing in this transition purports
to relicense that material.

2. Vadim Bulavintsev's historical contributions

All copyrightable contributions owned by Vadim Bulavintsev that were already
publicly released in the original history through commit
1c9a87bb61593494024810a450571f791374b05f are additionally offered under the
GNU Affero General Public License, version 3 (AGPL-3.0-only).

Those historical contributions remain available under GPL-3.0-or-later to
recipients of the earlier releases. No earlier license is revoked. A recipient
of historical material may therefore have rights under either license,
depending on the copy and licensing offer on which that recipient relies.

3. New maintainer contributions

Copyrightable contributions owned by Vadim Bulavintsev and first published
after this transition—not present in the original history through the commit
identified above—are licensed under AGPL-3.0-only unless a specific file notice
expressly says otherwise. They are not offered under GPL-3.0-or-later merely
because legacy GPL material remains in the repository.

This grant covers protectable human-authored expression and any copyrights or
related rights Vadim Bulavintsev owns in AI-assisted material. It does not
assert copyright over material that applicable law does not protect, and it
does not claim an AI system as an author or copyright holder.

4. New third-party contributions

Contributions accepted after this transition are licensed under
AGPL-3.0-only and are subject to CONTRIBUTING.md and CLA.md. Their actual
authors retain authorship and, unless separately assigned in writing,
copyright ownership.

5. Combined GPLv3/AGPLv3 work

Section 13 of GPLv3 permits GPLv3-covered work to be linked or combined with
AGPLv3-covered work. GPLv3 continues to govern the GPL-covered part, while the
special source-offer requirement in section 13 of AGPLv3 applies to the
combination as such when users interact with a modified version remotely over
a computer network.

The complete license texts are in:

  LICENSES/GPL-3.0-or-later.txt
  LICENSES/AGPL-3.0-only.txt

6. Additional terms and permissions

The reasonable project-provenance notice specified under section 7(b) of
GPLv3 and AGPLv3 is recorded in NOTICE.

The Apple Platforms and App Store Distribution Exception is in
LICENSES/LicenseRef-Apple-App-Store-Exception.txt. It preserves the historical
GPL permission verbatim and adds a section 7 permission for material owned by
Vadim Bulavintsev and for contributions accepted under CLA version 1.1, or a
later CLA version that expressly grants it. The exception permits
Apple-platform linking and App Store distribution without converting new
AGPL-covered source or executables to a proprietary licence. Its
source-availability and notice conditions remain mandatory.

Each copyright holder grants the exception only for material that holder owns
or is authorized to license. A distributor relying on it for a combined app
must ensure that every copyrightable part requiring an exception is covered by
the historical grant, the new grant, or another express grant from its holder.

7. Third-party material

Vendored packages, fonts, images, generated notices, and dependencies may be
under different licenses. Their own notices control. In particular, nothing
in this file relicenses material in a directory that contains a more specific
LICENSE file.
